## Live probing (source B) — hs_server.sh + sanctioned oracle binary
[L0] hs_server.sh start NSLPK3 3099 | FAILED: script passes `interactive <dir>
     --port <port>`; this tamarin build treats WORKDIR as the LAST positional and
     `--port <n>` (space form) leaves <n> as the workdir -> "directory '3099' does
     not exist." Recorded as a tooling bug in the provided oracle wrapper.
[L1] Start sanctioned binary with corrected args | same binary the script names,
     invoked as `interactive --port=3099 <tmpdir>` on NSLPK3.spthy. Server launched.
[L2] Probe routes not in captures |
       GET /                       -> 200 text/html "Welcome to the Tamarin prover"
                                      index page (theory table + upload form).
       GET /thy/trace/1/overview/help -> 200 text/html (matches page model).
       GET /thy/trace/%23/main/tactic -> 404 (literal '#' required; %23 rejected)
                                      => manifest key '#' is the capture tool's
                                      "current index" placeholder; real URLs use
                                      numeric indices.
       GET /thy/trace/1/main/nope   -> 404 full HTML page, echoes request path.
       GET /thy/trace/99/main/help  -> 404 (unknown theory index).
       GET /nonsense/path           -> 404.
[L3] Capture exact 404 body | saved as fixture notfound_nope.html (1272 bytes);
     templatized to NOT_FOUND with §PATH§ slot.
[L4] Save root index page for documentation | non-deterministic parts: theory-row
     load-time and origin temp path; static credits block otherwise fixed. Stopped server.

